 Re-mapping with preservation of relative phase and amplitude can be performed by means of optical dielectric waveguide fibers without explicit measurement of phases and amplitudes in the temporal Fourier plane. Alternatively, re-mapping can be performed by means of electrical conductors after measurement of phases and amplitudes in the temporal Fourier plane. 
